OL,4,C'Employers ignore you if they can't
OL,5,Cpronounce your surname'
OL,6, 21-year-old Mary Ibiyemi from Glasgow
OL,7, lost her job in a takeaway last year
OL,8, because her employer "just couldn't
OL,9, keep me on anymore" in the pandemic.
OL,11,FShe then spent fruitless months looking
OL,12,Ffor jobs, a time when her self-esteem
OL,13,F"just went down".
OL,15,FShe thinks it's hard for any young
OL,16,Fperson finding work at the moment, but
OL,17,Fparticularly if you are black.
OL,19,F"My surname isn't one a lot of people
OL,20,Fcan pronounce, and I feel employers are
OL,21,Fmore likely to skip over it," she said,
